episodes.overview: Interceptors join with the National Police Air Service to stop two suspects in a car believed to be on cloned plates - but that doesn't stop the driver taking the pursuit into fields

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: After speeding at over 100mph and driving on the wrong side of the road, the driver of a two-tonne pickup rams an interceptor's car before the rest of the team pitch in to help out.

episodes.name: Episode 10
episodes.overview: Firearms officers enter a property to discover an arsenal of weapons and a recently harvested cannabis crop, and suspicions are aroused by a lad in a balaclava on a sunny day.

episodes.name: Episode 11
episodes.overview: The Interceptors assemble to sting a motor suspected of carrying drugs. Plus how to stop a cloned 10-tonne lorry on the motorway.

episodes.name: Episode 12
episodes.overview: The team respond to reports of a shotgun changing hands in the suburbs. When the team swoops in, both buyer and seller are taken by surprise.

episodes.name: Episode 13
episodes.overview: A high-octane episode kicks off with the interceptors in hot pursuit. The lads abandon their car and disappear into the woods, however, the dog unit is dispatched to sniff them out.

episodes.name: Episode 14
episodes.overview: The interceptors are after a man wanted on suspicion of making threats to kill, who could be armed, and Coups and police dog Rambo are on the lookout for a suspected shoplifter.

episodes.name: Episode 15
episodes.overview: Units tail a van speeding at four times the limit. After the vehicle pops a tyre, the driver tries to flee as a three-wheeler, then on foot. But police dog Quantum is at his heels...

episodes.name: Episode 16
episodes.overview: Interceptors Gav and Neil pursue a pair of vehicles believed to have been involved in a raid on a car hire firm. Rob and Spence deal with a man hellbent on spitting at them.

episodes.name: Episode 17
episodes.overview: A runaway car speeds through the Nottinghamshire countryside, a routine stop turns nasty, and an artist in a rush is clocked speeding at over 100mph.

episodes.name: Episode 18
episodes.overview: Rich and Ash are after a potentially armed and dangerous man who is suspected of smashing up a property. Plus, Macca pursues a stolen Ford whose occupants leg it into a field in an attempt to escape.

episodes.name: Episode 19
episodes.overview: Two men in a van leave a trail of destruction during a 60-mile pursuit through four counties. The runaways ram multiple police cars before forcing Jon and Jules into a barrier at 70 mph.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Interceptor Bertie tails a fail-to-stop driver doing over a tonne. The chase ends with the car flipped onto its roof.

episodes.name: Episode 2
episodes.overview: A drink driver subjects Tarnia to a torrent of abuse - and saliva.

episodes.name: Episode 3
episodes.overview: Interceptors attend a prison where a man's seen tossing suspicious parcels over the wall.

episodes.name: Episode 4
episodes.overview: Police nab a van with no insurance, MOT, or tax. To top it off, the driver's been banned.

episodes.name: Episode 5
episodes.overview: A pair of potential car thieves are chased by pursuit units and drone.

episodes.name: Episode 6
episodes.overview: Familiar faces ride into town in tonight's episode, as the neighbours from Nottinghamshire pay a visit to Northants' patch.

episodes.name: Episode 7
episodes.overview: Paul 'Bertie' Bertram races to intercept a vehicle that's failed to stop. After the desperate driver's tyres are stung, he attempts a dash, but his getaway doesn't go to plan...

episodes.name: Episode 8
episodes.overview: This episode opens with a 100-mile-per-hour pursuit of an Audi A4 as Interceptors try to box in the motor on the M1, but the dangerous driver has other ideas.

episodes.name: Episode 9
episodes.overview: A  wanted man attempts to leg it, but is pursued by Sandra on foot, Tony with a drone, and dog handler Macca with his sniffer dog. Matt blows the whistle on match day drink driving.
